Before entering into a detailed discussion of the critical value of this MS„ Ι have to say a few words as to its general orthography. Generally speaking, it is much inferior to B in this respect: almost all the old spellings we find in B, are modernised in J. Our commentary will show that such forms as thesaurus adolescens auunculus surripio surripui surreptum cum etc. are much more frequent in J than then- saurus amaseam etc. as found in B.
